{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/post/erlang-docs-on-elixir-iex-shell/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<blockquote>\n<p>Note: Proceed if you're already using ASDF or Kerl for Elixir/Erlang Version Management</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Elixir is very well known for it's documentation and community involvement and most\nof the developers, when they adopt elixir, they first struggle to find the\nhelp documentation for erlang functions.</p>\n<p>We all would have come across this message when using:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-elixir\">iex(1)> h :heart\n**heart module not compiled with erlang docs \n</code></pre>\n<h2>So, how do we enable documentation for erlang functions:</h2>\n<p>The solution that I'm going to discuss is relevant with ASDF or Kerl.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Asdf is a popular version manager for multiple softwares.\nKerl is a popular version manager for erlang.\nAsdf internally uses kerl for downloading, building and installing erlang.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h4>Put this environment variable before installing erlang</h4>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">$ export KERL_BUILD_DOCS=yes\n</code></pre>\n<p>Before installing erlang the following packages are also needed for building documentation</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">$ apt install xsltproc fop\n</code></pre>\n<p>You need atleast erlang otp-23+ for enabling documentation</p>\n<h4>Reinstall Erlang and go into the Iex Shell:</h4>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 676px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cb126c35c0989ef3ead71cfe98c96b7d/9bb7a/2020-09-19-erlang-docs-elixir-iex-shell.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 95.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Erlang_Documentation_On_Elixir_Shell.png\"\n        title=\"Erlang_Documentation_On_Elixir_Shell.png\"\n        src=\"/static/cb126c35c0989ef3ead71cfe98c96b7d/9bb7a/2020-09-19-erlang-docs-elixir-iex-shell.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cb126c35c0989ef3ead71cfe98c96b7d/5a46d/2020-09-19-erlang-docs-elixir-iex-shell.png 300w,\n/static/cb126c35c0989ef3ead71cfe98c96b7d/0a47e/2020-09-19-erlang-docs-elixir-iex-shell.png 600w,\n/static/cb126c35c0989ef3ead71cfe98c96b7d/9bb7a/2020-09-19-erlang-docs-elixir-iex-shell.png 676w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 676px) 100vw, 676px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Hope, this helps some of you! Stay tuned for more.....</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Erlang Help Docs on Elixir Shell - Using ASDF or Kerl","date":"19 September, 2020","tags":["elixir","erlang","help","documentation","iex"]},"excerpt":"Note: Proceed if you're already using ASDF or Kerl for Elixir/Erlang Version Management Elixir is very well known for it's documentation andâ€¦"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/erlang-docs-on-elixir-iex-shell/","prev":{"fields":{"slug":"/xmpp-mongooseim-ejabberd-erlang-journey-part-2/"},"frontmatter":{"published":false}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/til-bookmarks-firefox-html-to-plain-file-and-manage-using-version-control/"},"frontmatter":{"published":true}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454"]}